{
  "texts": [
    "If there were a task-dependent evaluation bias, one could expect that the bias is consistent across m or n within a task, or there is a consistent pattern with how the bias changes with m or n across tasks.",
    "Figure 4 does not clearly support either of these hypotheses.",
    "Moscovich and Rosset (2022) found that the evaluation bias caused by unsupervised methods for tabular data converges to 0 as n increases.",
    "This finding is not confirmed by this experiment.",
    "§7 rules out undertraining on unlabeled text as the cause of a null evaluation bias."
  ]
}